<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 10:27AM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Lamar
County through 1100 AM CDT...
At 1027 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Millport, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Millport, Kennedy, Cody, Hightogy, Melborne and Star.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
